      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(anthropic): send current claude-cli user-agent on OAuth path",
        "body": "Closes #94716\n\n## What Problem This Solves\n\nFixes an issue where users authenticating to Anthropic through the `claude-cli` OAuth backend (`anthropic/claude-*` models with an `sk-ant-oat...` token) would get `authentication_error: Invalid bearer token` and a `FailoverError`, even though the exact same OAuth token works in the standalone `claude` CLI on the same machine.\n\nThe OAuth path advertised a hardcoded `user-agent: claude-cli/2.1.75` (an April-2025 build). Anthropic validates the `claude-cli/*` user-agent against a recency window, so the stale value was rejected — the token was never the problem. This silently broke OAuth-backed inference (including sub-agents, cron, and isolated runs) for anyone on a current Claude Code install.\n\n## Why This Change Was Made\n\nThe version was hardcoded in **two** independent places that had already drifted apart conceptually — `src/llm/providers/anthropic.ts` and `src/agents/anthropic-transport-stream.ts` — both emitting `claude-cli/2.1.75` on the OAuth bearer path.\n\nThis PR collapses them into a single source of truth, `src/llm/providers/claude-code-user-agent.ts`, which:\n\n- bumps the default to a current, accepted version (`2.1.177`, the version the reporter confirmed working), and\n- adds an `OPENCLAW_CLAUDE_CODE_VERSION` override so operators can match a future Anthropic bump **without waiting for a release**.\n\nDeliberate non-goal: I did **not** shell out to `claude --version` (the approach in the other open PRs on this issue). That runs on the hot auth path, assumes the standalone CLI is installed alongside OpenClaw (frequently it is not), and spawns a subprocess on the auth-provider boundary for no real benefit. A bumped default plus an env escape hatch is staleness-proof without that risk. API-key auth is untouched — only the `isOAuthToken(apiKey)` path changes.\n\n## User Impact\n\n- OAuth (`sk-ant-oat...`) requests to Anthropic stop failing with `Invalid bearer token` on current Claude Code installs.\n- If Anthropic tightens the window again, operators set `OPENCLAW_CLAUDE_CODE_VERSION=<semver>` and recover immediately — no new build required.\n- No change for Anthropic API-key auth or any non-Anthropic provider.\n\n## Real behavior proof\n\n- Behavior or issue addressed: The Anthropic OAuth bearer path no longer sends the stale `claude-cli/2.1.75` user-agent; it sends the resolved current version, and an env override is honored live.\n- Real environment tested: Windows 10 + Node, local checkout of this branch off `origin/main`.\n- Exact steps or command run after this patch:\n  ```bash\n  pnpm exec tsx scripts/proof-anthropic-oauth-user-agent.mts\n  ```\n  The harness calls the real `streamAnthropic()` OAuth path with a fake `sk-ant-oat...` token and stubs `globalThis.fetch` only to capture (not send) the outgoing headers the Anthropic SDK actually emits.\n- Evidence after fix:\n  ```text\n  default user-agent (OAuth path):          claude-cli/2.1.177\n  expected default:                         claude-cli/2.1.177\n  still sends stale claude-cli/2.1.75?       false\n\n  OPENCLAW_CLAUDE_CODE_VERSION=2.1.250 user-agent:  claude-cli/2.1.250\n\n  PROOF PASS\n  ```\n- Observed result after fix: The header that goes onto the wire for OAuth requests is now `claude-cli/2.1.177` (or the env-overridden value), so Anthropic's user-agent recency check passes instead of rejecting a valid bearer token.\n- Before evidence: On `origin/main`, both call sites build `claude-cli/${\"2.1.75\"}` (see `src/llm/providers/anthropic.ts` and `src/agents/anthropic-transport-stream.ts` before this diff), which is the rejected value reported in #94716.\n- What was not tested: A live round-trip against `api.anthropic.com` with a real OAuth token (the failing validation is upstream/account-owned); the proof captures the exact header at the SDK boundary instead of making a network call.\n\n## Tests and validation\n\n- `pnpm test src/llm/providers/claude-code-user-agent.test.ts src/llm/providers/anthropic.test.ts src/agents/anthropic-transport-stream.test.ts` — 118 passed.\n- New `claude-code-user-agent.test.ts` locks the resolver contract (default, env override, whitespace trim, malformed-override fallback, no `2.1.75`).\n- `anthropic.test.ts` adds an end-to-end assertion that the OAuth `new Anthropic(...)` config carries `user-agent: claude-cli/<default>` and never `2.1.75`.\n- Strengthened the existing transport-stream OAuth test to assert the exact resolved user-agent instead of a loose `toContain(\"claude-cli/\")`, covering the second call site.\n- `node scripts/run-oxlint.mjs <changed files>` — clean.\n- Live proof script above.\n\n## Risk checklist\n\n- Touches auth-provider boundary? Yes — only the Anthropic OAuth (`sk-ant-oat`) header. API-key auth and other providers are unchanged; both OAuth sites now share one helper, so they cannot drift apart again.\n- New config/env? One opt-in env var (`OPENCLAW_CLAUDE_CODE_VERSION`), validated as bare semver and ignored when malformed. It is a recovery escape hatch, not required for the fix to work.\n- Security boundary: No subprocess, no network, no secret handling changed. The user-agent is a non-secret identity header.\n- Highest-risk area: picking a default version that itself ages. Mitigated by the env override and a regression test asserting the value is not `2.1.75`.\n\n## Linked context\n\n- Related open PRs reviewed: #94719, #95187, #95205 — all resolve the version via `execSync(\"claude --version\")`. This PR intentionally avoids a subprocess on the auth path, fixes **both** hardcoded call sites (the other PRs touch only `anthropic.ts`), and adds a release-independent override. Thanks to those authors for confirming the root cause and the `2.1.177` working version.\n\n## Current review state\n\n- Next action: maintainer review.\n- Waiting on: nothing from author — fix, tests, lint, and live proof are in.\n- Bot comments addressed: opened with structured real-behavior proof (live SDK-boundary header capture) to avoid `mock-only-proof`.\n",
        "branch": "fix/anthropic-oauth-user-agent-version",
